&lt;h2 id=&#34;4-Perform-an-in-place-upgrade-installation&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#4-Perform-an-in-place-upgrade-installation&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;4. Perform an in-place upgrade installation&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;4. Perform an in-place upgrade installation&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can perform an in-place upgrade installation to repair a flaky existing install while keeping all your programs, personal data, and user accounts intact. To initiate in-place upgrade is easy, insert the Windows Installation disc or USB and Run setup.exe In the initial phase of the installation process, you must choose the &amp;#x2018;Upgrade&amp;#x2019; option to perform a repair install. &lt;img src=&#34;/2014/07/upgrade-windows.png&#34; alt=&#34;Upgrade Windows&#34;&gt; After the installation complete, clean up the old files using Disk Cleanup or Ccleaner. &lt;/p&gt;
